Bereaved and angry relatives flooded the airport in Larnaka, some collapsing in grief, as senior Greek ministers, including the country's prime minister, Kostas Karamanlis, broke off from their vacations to attend crisis talks in Athens.
9:00 a.m. (0600 GMT) _ Helios Airlines Flight ZU522, a Boeing 737, with 115 passengers and six crew members on board takes off from Larnaca International Airport in Cyprus, heading for Athens, Greece, and then Prague, Czech Republic.
It flies to Dublin, Ireland; Sofia, Bulgaria; Warsaw, Poland; Prague; Strasbourg, France; and several British airports.
